inline_comments.message:
Wayne, you're going to hate me for this but could we not just use the Pair class in Apache Commons?

See this example:

import org.apache.commons.lang3.tuple.MutablePair;
import org.apache.commons.lang3.tuple.Pair;

public class PairDeleteMe {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Pair<Integer, Integer> myPair = new MutablePair<>(1,2);

        if (myPair.getLeft() + myPair.getRight() != 3) {
            System.err.println("Somehow we are defying the laws of science, Jim");
        }
        else {
            System.err.println("All is well in the world, Jim");
        }
    }

}
